Add Organisation Hierarchy Relationship
post
/v1/organisation-hierarchies/relationship

üí° Operation ID: post-v1-organisation-hierarchies-relationships

üè∑Ô∏è Relationships

Creates a Organisation Hierarchy Relationship between two Organizations.
A Minority Shareholder Relationship exists when the parent Organisation does not hold majority control on an child Organisation and therefore owns 50% or less of the voting shares.
A Legal Immediate Parent Relationship exists when the Parent Organisation has majority control on an Child Organisation and therefore owns more than 50% of the voting shares, or, is able to control management and operations of that Child Organisation and/or financial accounts have been fully consolidated into financial accounts of the Parent Organisation.
Creates an Organisation Hierarchy Relationship between a parent Organizations and a child Organisation Unit.
A relationship between an Organisation and an Organisation Unit is used to identify the operating sites of an organisation, and therefore ownership percentage is not applicable. All relationships between Organisations and Organisation Units will have automatically a Legal Immediate Parent role type.
Creates an Organisation Hierarchy Relationship between a parent Individual and a child Organisation.
A relationship between an Individual and an Organisation is used to identify the natural persons who ultimately directly or indirectly have interest or control over a legal entity.
header params
X-ING-AccessToken string required
The access token identifying the worker

X-ING-LastUpdateUser string
Identifies the user, system, or process that last updated the instance of a data object. If not specified, the access token company key is used

Request body
The Organisation Hierarchy Relationship to add.


